msgstr "The chapter on confession (<i lang=\"pli\">pācittiya</i>)"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs0.4"
msgid "Ovādavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 27"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "27. Saṃvidhānasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on appointments"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs0.6"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "First sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.27.1"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.288"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="589"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya "
"ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjanti."
msgstr ""
"At that time the monks from the group of six traveled on a main road by "
"appointment with nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.4"
msgid ""
"“yatheva mayaṃ sapajāpatikā āhiṇḍāma, evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā "
"bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya āhiṇḍantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Just as we go around with our wives, so these Sakyan ascetics go around by "
"appointment with nuns.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="590"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.5"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.6"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.7"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.8"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya "
"ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“How can the monks from the group of six travel on a main road by "
"appointment with nuns?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.9"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya "
"ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.12"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya "
"ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissatha."
msgstr ""
"Foolish men, how can you travel on a main road by appointment with nuns?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.13"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.14"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha."
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Preliminary ruling"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="591"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.15"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ "
"paṭipajjeyya, antamaso gāmantarampi, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk travels on a main road by appointment with a nun, even if just "
"between villages, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </span>
#. </p><p class="endsection"><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="592"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs1.16"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr "In this way the Master laid down this training rule for the monks."

#. </p><h3>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Second sub-story"

#. </h3><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.63"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.27.2"></a> <a class="wt-pa" id="593"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.289"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca sāketā sāvatthiṃ "
"addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti."
msgstr ""
"Soon afterwards a number of monks and nuns were traveling from Sāketa to "
"Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.2"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The nuns said to the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.3"
msgid "“mayampi ayyehi saddhiṃ gamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "“We’ll go with you.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.4"
msgid ""
"“Na, bhaginī, kappati bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ "
"paṭipajjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Sisters, it’s not allowable for us to travel on a main road by appointment "
"with nuns."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.5"
msgid "Tumhe vā paṭhamaṃ gacchatha mayaṃ vā gamissāmā”ti."
msgstr "You should go first, or we will.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.6"
msgid "“Ayyā, bhante, aggapurisā."
msgstr "“Venerables, you have the highest status."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.7"
msgid "Ayyāva paṭhamaṃ gacchantū”ti."
msgstr "Please go first.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.8"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pacchā gacchantīnaṃ antarāmagge corā acchindiṃsu "
"ca dūsesuñca."
msgstr ""
"But because the nuns went behind, they were robbed and raped by bandits."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.9"
msgid ""
"Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"When they arrived at Sāvatthī, they told the nuns there what had happened."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.10"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "The nuns then told the monks,"

#. <a class="wt-pa" id="594"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.11"
msgid "Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "who in turn told the Master."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.13"
msgid ""
"“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, satthagamanīye magge sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye "
"bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjituṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Monks, I allow you to travel on a main road by appointment with a nun if it’"
"s a dangerous and frightening road that should be traveled with a group."

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.14"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "”And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.14a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="595"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.15"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ "
"paṭipajjeyya, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"‘If a monk travels on a main road by appointment with a nun, even if just "
"between villages, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits an "
"offense entailing confession."

#. <i lang="pli">Sattho</i>, often translated as caravan. According to <ref>Sp-ṭ.2.489</ref> this refers either to a caravan of travelers walking on foot or to a caravan of carts: <i lang="pli">satthoti jaṅghasattho sakaṭasattho vā</i>.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.16"
msgid ""
"Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Satthagamanīyo hoti maggo sāsaṅkasammato sappaṭibhayo—ayaṃ "
"tattha samayo”ti."
msgstr ""
"The appropriate reason is that the road is considered dangerous and "
"frightening and should be traveled with a group.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs2.17"
msgid "(<em>27</em>:<strong>76</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.27.3"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.27.3.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="596"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="597"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.6"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.7"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="598"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.8"
msgid "Saddhinti"
msgstr "With:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.9"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.290"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="599"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.10"
msgid "Saṃvidhāyāti—"
msgstr "By appointment: if he makes an appointment like this:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.11"
msgid ""
"“gacchāma, bhagini, gacchāmāyya; gacchāmāyya, gacchāma, bhagini; ajja vā "
"hiyyo vā pare vā gacchāmā”ti saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"he says, “Let’s go, Sister,” and she replies, “Yes, let’s go, Venerable;” or "
"she says, “Let’s go, Venerable,” and he replies, “Yes, let’s go, Sister;” or "
"he says, “Let’s go today/tomorrow/the day after tomorrow,” then he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="600"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.12"
msgid "Antamaso gāmantarampīti"
msgstr "Even if just between villages:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.13"
msgid "kukkuṭasampāte gāme, gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"when the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every village "
"interval he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. Half a <i lang="pli">yojana</i>. The length of a <i lang="pli">yojana</i> is uncertain, and perhaps it never was a precise distance. But a reasonable estimate is 8 miles or just under 13 kilometers (see ACMC, p.16). Thus half a <i lang="pli">yojana</i> is just over 6 km.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.14"
msgid "Agāmake araññe, addhayojane addhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is in an uninhabited area, in the wilderness, then for every six "
"kilometers he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="601"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.15"
msgid "Aññatra samayāti"
msgstr "Unless there is an appropriate reason:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.16"
msgid "ṭhapetvā samayaṃ."
msgstr "except at an appropriate time."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="602"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.17"
msgid "Satthagamanīyo nāma"
msgstr "The road […] should be traveled with a group:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.18"
msgid "maggo na sakkā hoti vinā satthena gantuṃ."
msgstr "it is not possible to travel without a group."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="603"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.19"
msgid "Sāsaṅkaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Dangerous:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: tasmiṃ magge → yasmiṃ magge (?)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.20"
msgid ""
"tasmiṃ magge corānaṃ niviṭṭhokāso dissati, bhuttokāso dissati, ṭhitokāso "
"dissati, nisinnokāso dissati, nipannokāso dissati."
msgstr ""
"thieves have been seen along that road, camped, eating, standing, seated, or "
"lying down."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.64"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="604"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.21"
msgid "Sappaṭibhayaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Frightening:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.22"
msgid ""
"tasmiṃ magge corehi manussā hatā dissanti, viluttā dissanti, ākoṭitā "
"dissanti, sappaṭibhayaṃ gantvā appaṭibhayaṃ dassetvā uyyojetabbā—"
msgstr ""
"thieves have been seen along that road, injuring, robbing, or beating "
"people. If they go thinking it is frightening, but then see that it is not, "
"the nuns are to be dismissed,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.1.23"
msgid "“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti."
msgstr "“Go, Sisters.”"

#. </span>
#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.27.3.2"></a> <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.291"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="605"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.2.1"
msgid ""
"Saṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso "
"gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is an appointment, and he perceives that there is, and he travels "
"on a main road with a nun, even if just between villages, unless there is an "
"appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.2.2"
msgid ""
"Saṃvidahite vematiko ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, "
"aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is an appointment, but he is unsure if there is, and he travels on "
"a main road with a nun, even if just between villages, unless there is an "
"appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.2.3"
msgid ""
"Saṃvidahite, asaṃvidahitasaññī ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso "
"gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is an appointment, but he perceives that there is not, and he "
"travels on a main road with a nun, even if just between villages, unless "
"there is an appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="606"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.2.4"
msgid "Bhikkhu saṃvidahati bhikkhunī na saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If the monk makes an appointment, but the nun does not express her "
"agreement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.2.5"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is no appointment, but he perceives that there is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.2.6"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If there is no appointment, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of "
"wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.2.7"
msgid "Asaṃvidahite asaṃvidahitasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If there is no appointment, and he perceives that there is not, there is no "
"offense."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.27.3.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="607"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.2"
msgid "samaye,"
msgstr "if there is an appropriate reason;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.3"
msgid "asaṃvidahitvā gacchati,"
msgstr "if he goes without an appointment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.4"
msgid "bhikkhunī saṃvidahati, bhikkhu na saṃvidahati,"
msgstr ""
"if the nun has made an appointment, but he has not expressed his agreement;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.5"
msgid "visaṅketena gacchanti,"
msgstr "if they go, but not according to the appointment;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.6"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.7"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.8"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="608"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc27:pts-cs3.3.9"
msgid "Saṃvidhānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ."
msgstr "The seventh rule, the training rule on appointments, is finished."

